RN  [1]
RM  17908933
RT  Defining the roles of the periplasmic chaperones SurA, Skp, and DegP in
RT  Escherichia coli.
RA  Sklar JG, Wu T, Kahne D, Silhavy TJ;
RL  Genes Dev. 2007;21:2473-2484.
CC  Outer membrane beta-barrel proteins are translocated into the periplasm
CC  by the Sec system and subsequently properly folded and inserted into
CC  the outer membrane by the beta-barrel assembly machine (Bam).  In the
CC  periplasm chaperones prevent misfolding and aggregation and facilitate
CC  the transit across the periplasmic space.  The SurA protein appears to
CC  be the primary chaperone, at least in E. coli [1], while Skp and DegP
CC  may act to rescue any OMPs which fall off of the SurA complex.
